# Mini App UI Rules

## Design system doc

Canonical reference: [DESIGN_SYSTEM.md](../../DESIGN_SYSTEM.md) (v1.8.5 shell + v2.1/v2.2 addenda). Token source: [apps/mini-app/src/style.css](../../apps/mini-app/src/style.css).

## v1.6 UI patterns

- **Milestone chip** (HUD) — `Manager in X.y` / `Director in X.y` / `CEO in X.y` progress during play
- **Death cause row** (game over) — icon + label per failure type
- **Retry tip** (game over) — satirical one-liner from `constants.ts`
- **Tap-zone glow** — `tap-zone-left/right:active` border feedback
- Co-branding: [`lib/branding.ts`](../../apps/mini-app/src/lib/branding.ts), `VITE_PROMPT_ANATOMY_URL` (optional env)

## v1.8.2 UI patterns (F&F bundle)

- **Tap deck** — `#tapControlsBar` with visible TAP LEFT / TAP RIGHT (snippet-style)
- **HUD tap hint** — `#hudTapHint` + `.tap-deck-hint` pulse for first 5 taps
- **HR memo rail** — in-run announcements below game HUD; `showHrMemoCombined()` for multi-line memos
- **Responsive ladder** — `#ladderTrack` fills shared content column at 320px / 390px
- **Home** — scroll on short Telegram viewports; amber news strip + shift description
- **Viewport QA** — `npm run qa:viewport` after layout changes (50% play-area ratio; tap deck outside `#gamePlayArea`)

## v1.8.3+ layout column

- **`#gameContentColumn`** — single `cl-shell-gutter` wraps HUD + play + tap (not per-section gutters)
- **Coffee pickup** — badge clears on collect; engine clears rung `coffee` flag

## v1.8.4 clip + reorg UX

- **REJECTED stamp** — fully visible inside `card-performance` (overflow visible)
- **HUD rank stack** — rank + milestone stacked; truncate + title tooltip on narrow phones
- **Play-area inset** — climber clamp; horizontal padding prevents sprite/hint clip
- **Frozen badge** — imminent reorg next rung labeled Frozen (no shuffle telegraph)

## v1.8.5 corridor + hazards

- **Center corridor** — `.player-at-corridor`, `.rung-center--corridor` before first tap; L/R control unchanged
- **`#imminentHint`** — next-rung panel through Intern phase (**40 rungs**); safe-side glow on imminent rung when `shouldShowImminentHint()` true
- **Obstacle badges** — slate **Gate** (Manager+), emerald **Plant** (CEO+); same dodge rules as meetings/deadlines
- **Layout QA** — `npm run qa:layout` after layout changes (post-tap width stable)
- **320×568** — compact HUD + tap deck; rung rows scale to 32px min so seven rungs fit

## v1.9 / v2.0 UI addenda

- **Sprint HUD chip** — Synergy Sprint wall-clock countdown
- **Revive button** — `#reviveAdBtn` “Mandatory HR Training” on qualifying game-over
- **Avatar picker** — `#avatarIconBtn` on home (localStorage emoji)
- **Game-over toast** — `.toast-above-game-over-actions` above RE-APPLY row
- **PA logo footer** — official Prompt Anatomy logo asset in `#homeBrandFooter`
- **Sound FAB** — visible in Telegram light theme

## v2.1 / v2.2 UI addenda

- **`#homeContextSlot`** — single rotating slot: news ticker, daily shift, challenge banner (6s crossfade); challenge pins until dismissed; daily shift static under reduced-motion
- **`#challengeBanner`** — incoming `startapp=c_*`; dismiss on tap or first Punch In
- **`.home-skeleton`** — Employee Badge fields pulse while `/auth/me` loads (no default pop-in)
- **`.home-hero-idle`** — briefcase hero micro-animation; disabled under reduced-motion and capture mode
- **`#homeGameplayPreview`** — collapses by default ≤620px only; taller viewports show full Avoid/Climb card
- **First-run tutorial** — glow-only safe-side buttons rungs 1–3; wrong-tap HR memo; no overlay card
- **`#reviveAdBtn`** — Mandatory HR Training; `.toast-above-game-over-actions` when ad unavailable
- **Landscape** — portrait gate on squashed landscape viewports; shell `min-height: 100dvh`
- **Android dark theme** — `.cl-viewport` and WebApp background stay light so slate shell copy stays readable

Canonical: [DESIGN_SYSTEM.md](../../DESIGN_SYSTEM.md). Do not regress without [ROADMAP.md](../../ROADMAP.md) baseline update.

## Structure (unchanged)

See [mini-app-frontend.mdc](mini-app-frontend.mdc) for folder layout and game/API rules.

## Agent must do

- Use `@utility` classes from `style.css` for shell UI (buttons, cards, typography, badges)
- Use `text-micro`, `text-caption`, `text-nano` — never `text-[NNpx]`
- Add `focus-ring` to new shell interactives
- Use `min-h-[44px]` on shell buttons (except game tap zones and LB tab pills)
- Preserve Telegram `--cl-*` theme integration via existing `.cl-*` shell classes
- Use `brand-attribution-*` utilities for Prompt Anatomy footer on shell screens only
- Update DESIGN_SYSTEM.md when adding utilities
- Run `npm run build`; after layout changes run `npm run qa:viewport` and `npm run qa:layout`

## Agent must not do

- Invent hex/rgba colors in `template.ts` or `app.ts`
- Duplicate card/button recipes inline (use `card-light`, `btn-cl-primary`, etc.)
- Import Prompt Anatomy navy/gold brand or ecosystem phase colors **as game primary palette**
- Redesign game HUD or tap zones without explicit request
- Change mechanics per [ROADMAP](../../ROADMAP.md) § Shipped baseline; scope check [mvp-scope](../../docs/mvp-scope.md)

## Allowed patterns

```html
<!-- Primary CTA -->
<button class="btn-cl-primary w-full py-4">...</button>

<!-- Light card -->
<div class="card-light space-y-3">...</div>

<!-- Rank badge (via app.ts RANK_BADGE map) -->
<span class="badge-rank-intern mt-0.5">...</span>
```

## Forbidden patterns

```html
<!-- ❌ Ad-hoc primary button -->
<button class="bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 ...">

<!-- ❌ Ad-hoc micro type -->
<span class="text-[10px]">

<!-- ❌ Duplicate card shell -->
<div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-4 shadow-sm">
```

